items.badge_description: You may not be able to see through the haze, but that juicy, hoppy goodness goes down smooth. What started as a trend is here to stay. That's 165 different beers with the style of IPA - New England / Hazy, Pale Ale - New England / Hazy, IPA - Milkshake, or Pale Ale - Milkshake. Try 5 more for Level 34!
It takes the perfect amount of light, the right framing and a touch of creative love to get the perfect picture of your brew. Now it’s time to drink it! That’s 110 check-ins with a photo.

When a single isn’t enough, make it a double. Doubling the hops and malts in a recipe results in a higher ABV and can pack quite a boozey punch. That's 30 different beers with the style that contains Imperial / Double in its style name. Try 5 more for Level 7!

You’ve pledged allegiance, and now it’s time to enjoy some beer! Now remember, not all American beer is fizzy and yellow. That’s 125 different beers from a brewery in the United States. Try 5 more for Level 26.

Everyone loves fresh beer, but obviously not as much as you do. You went straight to the source. 

That's a beer at 60 different venues categorized as a Brewery, Cidery or Meadery. Visit 5 more for Level 13!

At a new place and don't want to choose a pint of something you may not like? Grab a few tasters! Enjoy some small pours and then decide which to upgrade to a full pour. That's 5 checkins with the serving style of Taster. Try 5 more for Level 2! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

beer.beer_description: Special release of the Oatmeal Stout aged in a blend of Bear Republic and Four Roses barrels.

items.badge_description:
Thank you for celebrating International Stout Day by savoring a delicious stout! Stout enthusiasts like you know that there's a world of flavor waiting to be explored within the stout family, from classic dry stouts to rich barrel-aged stouts, and everything in between. Here's a toast to the deep, complex, and delightful world of stouts!

Keep exploring the rich, roasted flavors and aromatic notes that stouts have to offer, and earn other great stout badges like Beyond a Shadow of a Stout, Heavy Weight, Dessert Time! and more.

Porters and Stouts are rich with both history and flavor. Roasty, dark, and delicious, these two styles helped start it all. That’s 75 different beers with the style of Porter or Stout. Try 5 more for Level 16!
